03:32.413 --> 03:34.815
Okay, you're on your way home?

03:35.916 --> 03:37.718
All right, well I will, uh,

03:37.818 --> 03:39.887
hold down the fort
until you get back.

03:39.987 --> 03:41.555
Okay, see you soon.

03:51.499 --> 03:54.268
The trail derailed
just outside of Clinton.

03:54.368 --> 03:56.804
Eyewitness reported
a massive fireball.

03:56.904 --> 04:00.541
Many residents of the local
area have already been removed.

04:00.641 --> 04:02.876
Now, representatives from
the railroad have not yet

04:02.976 --> 04:04.478
been reached for comment.

04:04.578 --> 04:06.780
Many local residents
left shaken.

04:06.880 --> 04:09.249
Now this train accident is
being deemed one of the worst

04:09.350 --> 04:11.251
in the state's history.

04:11.352 --> 04:13.421
There is no telling yet
how this is gonna impact

04:13.521 --> 04:14.855
the local commun...

04:20.394 --> 04:23.397
(suspenseful music)

04:40.080 --> 04:43.283
(clunking upstairs)

04:45.085 --> 04:48.288
(suspenseful music)

05:12.713 --> 05:15.315
(door slams)

05:34.468 --> 05:35.335
Megan?

05:40.474 --> 05:41.341
Ricky?

05:44.612 --> 05:45.479
Megan?

05:55.188 --> 05:56.056
Ricky?

06:00.494 --> 06:01.862
Ricky.

06:01.962 --> 06:03.764
You scared me.

06:03.864 --> 06:04.898
What are you doing?

06:04.998 --> 06:06.800
You need to go to bed.

06:07.768 --> 06:10.370
Why are you dressed like that?

06:12.205 --> 06:15.609
You better be
running to your room!

06:15.709 --> 06:18.646
(suspenseful music)

06:39.533 --> 06:41.669
(rattling)

06:55.949 --> 06:56.817
Ricky?

07:01.555 --> 07:03.557
Ricky, this isn't funny.

07:18.772 --> 07:20.974
(laughing)

07:41.161 --> 07:44.164
(suspenseful music)

08:12.626 --> 08:14.762
(screams)

08:17.765 --> 08:20.200
(creepy music)

10:24.024 --> 10:27.294
(general diner chatter)

10:36.469 --> 10:39.039
[Dylan] Are you gonna
finish that or what?

10:39.139 --> 10:39.907
Yup.

10:42.309 --> 10:44.678
[Dylan] Are you
gonna do that today?

10:44.778 --> 10:45.779
Yeah.

10:45.879 --> 10:46.914
You eat too fast.

10:47.014 --> 10:48.148
You eat too slow.

10:48.248 --> 10:49.917
We got shit to do, man.

10:50.017 --> 10:51.184
I don't wanna be here all day.

10:51.284 --> 10:54.054
Be nice to get home
by dark for once.

10:54.154 --> 10:56.323
But if you worked
a little faster,

10:56.423 --> 10:58.759
we'd get home at a decent time.

10:58.859 --> 10:59.760
I work slow?

10:59.860 --> 11:01.028
[Billy] Yeah.

11:01.128 --> 11:02.029
Really?

11:02.129 --> 11:03.363
[Billy] Uh-huh.

11:10.203 --> 11:13.173
(clattering dishes)

11:13.273 --> 11:15.876
[Diner] Cleanup in aisle six!

11:20.814 --> 11:21.915
Afternoon folks.

11:22.015 --> 11:23.350
What are you kids up to today?

11:23.450 --> 11:25.218
Concert in Columbus,
headed up that way.

11:25.318 --> 11:26.386
Ah, gotcha.

11:26.486 --> 11:28.121
I'm gonna hit the head.

11:28.221 --> 11:29.122
Yeah me, too.

11:29.222 --> 11:31.424
You two have fun in there.

11:34.494 --> 11:35.362
Sorry.

11:42.369 --> 11:43.236
Oh god.

11:48.241 --> 11:49.109
Mike.

11:49.209 --> 11:50.377
[Mike] Mm.

11:50.477 --> 11:51.845
Check it out.

11:53.246 --> 11:54.948
What do you think?

11:55.048 --> 11:56.716
[Mike] I think the
answer's still no,

11:56.817 --> 11:58.385
I'm not marrying you.

11:58.485 --> 11:59.953
It's for Sarah, idiot.

12:00.053 --> 12:01.721
I know that.

12:01.822 --> 12:03.356
We've been together
for almost two years

12:03.456 --> 12:04.324
and I think it's time.

12:04.424 --> 12:06.493
You, you and I have
been together for,

12:06.593 --> 12:09.429
I don't even know how
many years anymore.

12:09.529 --> 12:11.398
I've been trying to figure
out when the right time is.

12:11.498 --> 12:14.868
I feel like tonight's the night.

12:14.968 --> 12:16.736
She's gonna say yes.

12:16.837 --> 12:17.737
Lemme see.

12:20.073 --> 12:21.842
I don't know, man.

12:21.942 --> 12:24.377
I'm just trying to enjoy
life at this point.

12:24.477 --> 12:25.412
It's pretty.

12:27.180 --> 12:29.149
You ever thought
about it with Jill?

12:29.249 --> 12:30.183
No.

12:30.283 --> 12:31.384
No, it's been like eight months,

12:31.484 --> 12:33.153
I have not thought
about it with Jill.

12:33.253 --> 12:35.255
Are you sure you wanna
do it on this trip?

12:35.355 --> 12:36.924
Yes, that's my plan.

12:37.024 --> 12:40.060
Oh, please, please don't
do it on this trip, dude.

12:40.160 --> 12:41.061
[Brad] Why?

12:41.161 --> 12:43.296
Because, you two are
gonna start crying,

12:43.396 --> 12:45.032
and then Jill's gonna
start crying and

12:45.132 --> 12:48.135
then I'm not gonna cry, I'm
gonna look like an asshole.

12:48.235 --> 12:49.169
So what?

12:49.269 --> 12:50.303
It's not about you.

12:50.403 --> 12:51.905
It's about Sarah.

12:53.306 --> 12:55.408
You know how much I love her.

12:55.508 --> 12:57.277
No, no, I, you guys
are great together,

12:57.377 --> 12:59.913
she's a great girl, I got
nothing but good things to say.

13:00.013 --> 13:01.348
All right.

13:01.448 --> 13:03.350
If you are serious about
this, I do have one

13:03.450 --> 13:05.418
piece of advice for you.

13:05.518 --> 13:08.288
What's your one
piece of advice, Mike?

13:08.388 --> 13:09.957
(loud fart)

13:10.057 --> 13:11.024
Are you serious?

13:11.124 --> 13:13.226
(laughter)

13:14.594 --> 13:17.464
Hey, my water glass is empty,
think I could get a refill?

13:17.564 --> 13:19.366
[Waitress] I'll be
there in a minute!

13:19.466 --> 13:20.934
You boys have fun it there?

13:22.102 --> 13:22.569
Brad just had something
important he wanted to tell me.

13:22.669 --> 13:24.171
Dude.

13:25.405 --> 13:27.307
He just wanted to make sure
he was still bigger than me.

13:27.407 --> 13:28.041
Sorry about that.

13:28.141 --> 13:30.110
Oh, you're as quick as a fox.

13:30.210 --> 13:31.311
I try to be.

13:31.411 --> 13:33.847
Just let me know if I can
get you guys anything else.

13:33.947 --> 13:34.814
[Billy] Just the bill, please.

13:34.915 --> 13:35.448
Okay.

13:35.548 --> 13:36.984
[Billy] Thanks.

13:42.355 --> 13:45.092
Ma'am, could you tell
us how to get to the 137?

13:45.192 --> 13:46.927
We're trying to get to
Columbus but my phone keeps

13:47.027 --> 13:48.261
going in and out.

13:49.429 --> 13:52.265
It does that here, sweetheart,
it's called Southern Ohio.

13:52.365 --> 13:54.201
You ladies
heading to Columbus?

13:54.301 --> 13:55.468
Yes, we are.

13:55.568 --> 13:57.837
I can get you
there a lot quicker.

13:57.938 --> 14:00.974
You're gonna take the
highway south two exits,

14:01.074 --> 14:04.844
gonna turn right, go down
two streets and turn left.

14:04.945 --> 14:07.247
That puts you
right to route 137.

14:07.347 --> 14:08.381
You got that?

14:10.450 --> 14:13.320
That sounds like
in makes sense.

14:16.389 --> 14:17.257
Really?

14:19.592 --> 14:22.262
Hey, is there a problem here?

14:28.168 --> 14:29.269
No problem.

14:34.141 --> 14:35.642
I apologize for some
of the trailer trash

14:35.742 --> 14:37.377
that pass along through here.

14:37.477 --> 14:38.979
They don't know how
to treat a lady.

14:40.213 --> 14:40.647
You guys are headed down to
Columbus if I heard correctly?

14:41.581 --> 14:42.182
Yeah, trying to
make it to a concert.

14:43.383 --> 14:44.384
Well I wouldn't take the
137, there's some construction

14:45.585 --> 14:47.154
down there and I've, uh, gotten
some reports of some delays.

14:47.254 --> 14:48.555
I just wouldn't
chance it in a hurry.

14:48.655 --> 14:49.656
Do you know a better way?

14:49.756 --> 14:51.024
Well there's a faster way.

14:52.259 --> 14:52.892
Takes you to some small towns,
it's pretty easy to miss a,

14:53.826 --> 14:55.562
uh, turn you can get
lost, but it is faster.

14:55.662 --> 14:57.097
Up to you, though.

14:58.331 --> 14:59.066
I'm pretty sure we want to
get there as fast as possible.

14:59.166 --> 15:00.267
Do it.

15:00.367 --> 15:03.236
Alright, well lemme
see your map here.

15:07.307 --> 15:09.909
All right, that should be easy
enough for you to figure out.

15:10.010 --> 15:11.478
Thanks, Sheriff, we
appreciate the help.

15:11.578 --> 15:13.013
I just wouldn't
screw around in any of

15:13.113 --> 15:14.147
those small towns, though. It's.

15:14.247 --> 15:15.615
It's pretty easy
to get sidetracked.

15:15.715 --> 15:17.450
Nah, you've seen one backwater
town you've seen 'em all.

15:17.550 --> 15:19.152
Mike.

15:19.252 --> 15:20.153
[Mike] What?

15:20.253 --> 15:21.154
It's Ohio.

15:21.254 --> 15:22.322
Well, suit yourself.

15:22.422 --> 15:24.491
You guys have a safe trip.

15:26.726 --> 15:29.929
(suspenseful music)

15:31.664 --> 15:34.667
(branches breaking)

15:35.735 --> 15:38.938
(suspenseful music)

16:28.655 --> 16:31.058
(gurgling)

16:38.065 --> 16:41.501
* She's a hell bound sling

16:41.601 --> 16:44.671
* Burning up the line

16:46.139 --> 16:49.242
* Can't flag her down

16:49.342 --> 16:51.511
* She ain't got the time

16:51.611 --> 16:53.713
(laughter)

16:55.548 --> 16:57.150
Oh god.

16:57.250 --> 16:59.286
And then you woke up in the
morning and you, (laughter)

16:59.386 --> 17:02.289
you went to your sock drawer
and it was soaking wet

17:02.389 --> 17:04.057
and you're like, oh.

17:05.358 --> 17:07.327
But you didn't realize
babe that you were so drunk

17:07.426 --> 17:09.596
you had woken up in the middle
of the night to take a piss

17:09.695 --> 17:12.665
and you thought that your
sock drawer was the toilet.

17:12.765 --> 17:14.701
My sock drawer
is this tall on me.

17:14.800 --> 17:17.304
Like, I have no idea how
I even got up that high.

17:17.404 --> 17:19.571
Wait, is that the same
night that Brad went to bed

17:19.672 --> 17:21.741
wearing that ridiculous hat?

17:21.840 --> 17:22.809
[Jill] Yeah.

17:22.909 --> 17:24.176
Yes, yes it is.

17:24.277 --> 17:26.279
The furry hat, the babushka hat.

17:26.378 --> 17:29.282
(laughter)

17:29.382 --> 17:32.185
I've never seen
Brad that drunk.

17:32.852 --> 17:36.456
* And you don't wanna ride

17:36.556 --> 17:40.627
* Around the devil's train.

17:44.897 --> 17:46.566
I've gotta get gas soon.

17:46.666 --> 17:49.469
Well I can see if I can find
a gas station on my phone.

17:49.569 --> 17:51.070
Thank you, baby.

17:57.477 --> 17:58.711
What's wrong?

17:58.811 --> 18:00.313
[Jill] Uh, I
can't find my phone.

18:00.413 --> 18:01.848
[Mike] What do you mean
you can't find your phone?

18:01.948 --> 18:04.717
I mean I cant find my phone.

18:04.817 --> 18:05.785
[Mike] Great.

18:06.886 --> 18:07.587
Oh shit, guys, will you
look and see if my phone

18:08.255 --> 18:10.089
is back there by any chance?

18:11.391 --> 18:12.359
Shit.

18:13.326 --> 18:13.626
Babe, pull over, I've
gotta have my phone,

18:14.861 --> 18:15.795
it's got my credit card and
my IDs and all my shit in it.

18:16.796 --> 18:19.499
[Mike] I know, I know,
I know, I know, I know.

18:19.599 --> 18:20.367
Fuck.

18:31.511 --> 18:32.379
Ugh, fuck.

18:34.647 --> 18:36.115
[Sarah] Did you
have it at the diner?

18:36.216 --> 18:37.884
Yeah, I mean I pulled
it out when we asked

18:37.984 --> 18:39.519
the waitress for directions.

18:39.619 --> 18:42.789
Shit, I put it on
the counter and then

18:42.889 --> 18:45.124
that creepy guy walked up.

18:45.225 --> 18:46.259
I must've left it there, shit!

18:46.359 --> 18:47.627
It's okay.

18:47.727 --> 18:49.229
I'm sure she picked it
up and she's probably

18:49.329 --> 18:50.763
just waiting for us
to go back and get it.

18:50.863 --> 18:52.565
If we go back now we're
gonna miss the show.

18:52.665 --> 18:54.234
Babe, what am
I supposed to do?

18:54.334 --> 18:55.535
It's got my ID in it.

18:55.635 --> 18:56.903
I don't know, I'm just saying.

18:57.003 --> 18:58.905
Guys, why don't we
just call the phone?

18:59.005 --> 19:00.507
See if the waitress has it.

19:00.607 --> 19:02.375
If she does, we'll just
pick it up on the way back

19:02.475 --> 19:03.243
from the concert.

19:03.343 --> 19:04.411
That's fine.

19:12.219 --> 19:13.186
[Man] Hello?

19:13.286 --> 19:14.321
Hello?

19:14.421 --> 19:15.488
Hi.

19:15.588 --> 19:17.557
Uh, my friend lost her phone
and this is her number.

19:17.657 --> 19:19.726
[Man] Yes, I believe I
have your friend's phone.

19:19.826 --> 19:22.595
Did you find it in the diner?

19:22.695 --> 19:23.496
Hello?

19:24.997 --> 19:26.399
Are you there?

19:26.499 --> 19:27.834
[Man] Where are you?

19:27.934 --> 19:29.836
I don't know,
we're on some road.

19:29.936 --> 19:32.405
We just wanna get the
phone back, please.

19:32.505 --> 19:33.706
[Man] Where are you?

19:33.806 --> 19:36.276
Guys, where the hell are we?

19:36.376 --> 19:37.444
[Brad] Who's on the phone?

19:37.544 --> 19:38.711
I don't know,
it's just some guy,

19:38.811 --> 19:39.946
he keeps asking me where we are.

19:40.046 --> 19:41.581
We're like 10 miles
east of Route 37.

19:41.681 --> 19:43.583
I think we're on Bradley?

19:43.683 --> 19:48.488
We're about 10 miles east
of Route 37 on Bradley Road.

19:48.588 --> 19:50.457
[Man] I can meet you
and return your phone.

19:50.557 --> 19:52.559
Oh, well why don't we
just meet you at the diner?

19:52.659 --> 19:53.860
[Man] No, keep driving.

19:53.960 --> 19:55.962
You'll pass a sign before
the railroad tracks.

19:56.062 --> 19:59.299
Turn left, go into town,
and meet me at 5th and Main.

19:59.399 --> 20:00.867
I'll be waiting.

20:00.967 --> 20:02.602
Okay, so we drive
down to where?

20:02.702 --> 20:03.503
Hello?

20:05.738 --> 20:06.606
Hello?

20:09.476 --> 20:10.710
He hung up.

20:10.810 --> 20:11.878
Well what'd he say?

20:12.879 --> 20:14.347
He said that there's
a town just up ahead,

20:15.448 --> 20:17.317
at an intersection, and
he's gonna meet us there.

20:17.417 --> 20:18.485
That's awesome.

20:19.452 --> 20:21.788
Let's do it, come on,
we're already late.

20:28.761 --> 20:31.764
(suspenseful music)

20:41.641 --> 20:43.510
Looks like we're here.

20:57.990 --> 21:00.259
So where is this guy?

21:00.360 --> 21:02.028
This is where the
guy wanted to meet.

21:02.128 --> 21:04.531
He better show,
he's got all my info.

21:04.631 --> 21:06.699
I can't believe I
fucking left it there.

21:06.799 --> 21:09.569
I'll try calling him again
and seeing if he's close.

21:09.669 --> 21:11.638
Just see where he's at.

21:11.738 --> 21:15.542
Oh, I have no signal,
guys, do you have one?

21:16.976 --> 21:17.910
No.

21:18.010 --> 21:18.811
Nothing.

21:20.347 --> 21:21.614
He's gonna show.

21:25.618 --> 21:27.286
I can't believe
this is happening.

21:27.387 --> 21:28.821
I'm so sorry, guys.

21:31.558 --> 21:34.561
(suspenseful music)

21:47.707 --> 21:50.410
I don't get it,
where is everybody?

21:50.510 --> 21:52.078
[Mike] I don't know,
babe but it's like,

21:52.178 --> 21:54.714
it's like they all just left.

22:01.988 --> 22:04.323
I mean, he has to
show up, right?

22:04.424 --> 22:07.560
I mean why the hell else would
he tell us to meet him here?

22:07.660 --> 22:10.597
(suspenseful music)

22:15.468 --> 22:17.604
[Jill] This is bullshit.

22:24.176 --> 22:25.612
[Brad] Hello?

22:31.918 --> 22:33.653
Anything?

22:33.753 --> 22:34.353
No.

22:35.622 --> 22:37.724
Let's just chill for a bit.

22:37.824 --> 22:39.459
This guy's gotta show up.

22:39.559 --> 22:40.893
We can sit by the gazebo.

22:40.993 --> 22:43.396
[Brad] That's a good idea.

22:57.977 --> 22:59.679
Anybody want some?

23:01.948 --> 23:03.416
I need to relax.

23:04.651 --> 23:07.620
I cannot believe I
left my damn phone.

23:07.720 --> 23:09.388
It's fine, seriously.

23:09.489 --> 23:10.490
Don't worry about it.

23:10.590 --> 23:12.058
This guy's gonna show up.

23:12.158 --> 23:15.428
Listen, baby, I
am not in the mood.

23:15.528 --> 23:17.664
That's what you said
on our first date.

23:17.764 --> 23:18.931
Oh, well that's when
I thought you were

23:19.031 --> 23:20.399
still going places.

23:20.500 --> 23:21.568
Ow.

23:21.668 --> 23:22.769
You thought he
was going places?

23:22.869 --> 23:24.070
How much did you
smoke that night?

23:24.170 --> 23:25.171
I went to college.

23:25.271 --> 23:26.839
Shoulda stayed gone.

23:26.939 --> 23:30.943
Oh, poor baby, let's
leave the poor baby alone.

23:34.847 --> 23:37.850
(suspenseful music)

23:56.969 --> 23:57.970
Are you gonna share that?

23:58.070 --> 23:59.071
